definitions.definition: A light meal usually eaten around midday , notably when not as main meal of the day.
A break in play between the first and second sessions .
Any small meal, especially one eaten at a social gathering .
examples: After the funeral there was a lunch for those who didn't go to the cemetery.

definitions.definition: A thin piece or hunk ( of bread, meat, etc. )

main_definition: A light meal usually eaten around midday , notably when not as main meal of the day.
